In a speech delivered at the White House, First Lady Jill Biden discusses the impact of cancer and the importance of finding a cure. She shares personal experiences of friends who have battled cancer and emphasizes the need for prevention and education. Biden highlights the progress being made in cancer research and the collaborative efforts needed to combat the disease. She expresses her commitment to the Cancer Moonshot initiative and calls for unity in rewriting the story of cancer. Vice President Kamala Harris, who also has personal experience with cancer, follows Biden's speech and emphasizes the hope that can be found in the scientific community.